'''''Star Wars'' 17''' is the seventeenth issue in the ''[[Star Wars: Republic]]'' series of comics. It was published on [[April 26]], [[2000]] by [[Dark Horse Comics]].

==Publisher's summary==
''After encountering monstrous akk dogs under the command of the Red Iaro Terrorists, Mace Windu and his former Padawan Depa Billaba go in search of a smuggling ring that's transporting the animals from Mace's homeworld and turning them into savage pit-fighting beasts. But the corridors and depths of the Smuggler's Moon are havens of scum and villainy--no place for Jedi!''

==Plot summary==
Shortly after reaching Nar Shaddaa, Mace Windu attempts to stop a man from killing an [[Aunuanna|old beggar woman]]. When Master Windu suddenly finds himself outgunned, Billaba reveals her presence. After the remaining thugs are chased off, a third, mysterious Jedi appears and gives them information on their search for the [[Akk dog/Legends|akk dogs]]. Grateful to the Jedi, the old woman gives them one of her only possessions: an old [[Swoop/Legends|swoop]], with which to reach the lower levels. As the two Masters approach their destination, they are attacked by vicious [[Vrblther/Legends|vrblthers]].

